
#### Ansible Adhoc commands ####

1. To get uptime of the system
% ansible localhost -m command -a uptime
                                                                                                                                                                  ✭
[WARNING]: No inventory was parsed, only implicit localhost is available
localhost | CHANGED | rc=0 >>
14:56  up  4:42, 2 users, load averages: 1.90 2.72 3.00

 
(base) [balaji@balajis-MacBook-Air:~/Development/gitfolder/ansible on master]

2. to get date of the system
% ansible localhost -a date                                                                                                                                                                               ✭
[WARNING]: No inventory was parsed, only implicit localhost is available
localhost | CHANGED | rc=0 >>
Mon Oct 31 14:57:08 IST 2022

3. to get gather facts of the system

ansible localhost -m ansible.builtin.setup

4. to get logged in user details

% ansible localhost -m ansible.builtin.shell -a 'echo $USER'                                                   ✭
[WARNING]: No inventory was parsed, only implicit localhost is available
localhost | CHANGED | rc=0 >>
balaji

5. to create a test.txt file

ansible localhost -m shell -a "touch test.txt"
[WARNING]: No inventory was parsed, only implicit localhost is available
localhost | CHANGED | rc=0 >>


6.✗ ansible localhost -a uptime
[WARNING]: No inventory was parsed, only implicit localhost is available
